visual_elements.description: Figure 29: A plan view diagram illustrating the dimensions for a carport parking space. It shows a car parked within a rectangular space. The space is defined by two corner columns on one side and a solid wall or boundary on the other. A 'Driveway/parking surface' is indicated leading to the space. Dimensions include a '20' min. open' length along the side of the car and an 'open' width for entry/exit. An arrow points from 'One of 2 corner columns' to one of the columns.

Figure 30 (Top): A left side elevation diagram illustrating dimensions for a covered parking space. It shows a car parked under a sloped roof supported by columns. Dimensions include a '20' min. open' horizontal length for the covered area and a '7' min. open' vertical clearance from the ground to the bottom of the roof system. Arrows point from 'One of 2 corner columns' to a column and from 'Bottom roof system' to the underside of the roof.

Figure 30 (Bottom): A front elevation diagram illustrating dimensions for a covered parking space. It shows a car parked under a sloped roof supported by columns. Dimensions include a '10' min open' horizontal width for the covered area and a '7' min. open' vertical clearance from the ground to the bottom of the roof system. Arrows point from 'One of 2 corner columns' to a column and from 'Bottom roof system' to the underside of the roof.
